$string['choosereadme'] = '<div class="clearfix"><div class="theme_screenshot"><h2>Strawberry</h2><img src="strawberry/pix/screenshot.png" /><h3>Theme Discussion Forum:</h3><p><a href="http://moodle.org/mod/forum/view.php?id=46" target="_blank">http://moodle.org/mod/forum/view.php?id=46</a></p><h3>Theme Documentation:</h3><p><a href="http://docs.moodle.org/en/Themes" target="_blank">http://docs.moodle.org/en/Themes</a></p><h3>Report a bug:</h3><p><a href="http://tracker.moodle.org" target="_blank">http://tracker.moodle.org</a></p></div><div class="theme_description"><h2>About</h2><p>Strawberry is a fluid-width, three-column theme for Moodle 2.2 or higher. The custom menu contains a Home link which always appears to the very left, and a My courses and Login/Logout link, which appears after any administrator-added items.</p><p>Strawberry has a settings page that lets you modify various background colours, custom footer, custom css, and the site logo.</p><h2>Tweaks</h2><p>This theme is built upon Base, a parent theme included in the Moodle core. If you want to modify Strawberry, we recommend that you first duplicate it then rename it before making your changes. This means you\'ll still have the original files if you make a mistake. More information on modifying themes can be found in the <a href="http://docs.moodle.org/en/Theme">MoodleDocs</a>.</p><h2>Credits</h2><p>This theme uses the design of Strawberry theme from <a href="http://www.templatemo.com" target="_blank">Templatemo.com</a>, but none of the actual code from that theme was used.</p><p>Images are from the Strawberry theme from Templatemo, except the default banner. That image is attributed to <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/w-j-s" target="_blank">W.J.S on Flickr</a>. The image allows for non-commercial use with attribution.</p><p>This theme was coded and is maintained by Miriam Laidlaw of HRDNZ. She can be contacted by email at miriam@hrdnz.com.</p></div></div>';

